            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lessons & Memory"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agents can use several complementary memory types: working memory (the live conversation), episodic memory (lessons from past runs), semantic memory (durable domain facts), and procedural memory (tool schemas and instructions). Combining them creates agents that improve over time rather than starting fresh on every run."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Memory taxonomy for agents",
          "title": "Four memory types assembled into a system prompt"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Key distinction: "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "episodic memory holds "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "italic"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "lessons"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " (strategies that transfer); semantic memory holds "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "italic"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "facts"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " (domain knowledge that stays true). Mixing them produces context that is both noisy and hard to maintain."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
