      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Token budget: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "a combined memory context of 500\u2013800 tokens is a reasonable ceiling. Beyond that, system prompt cost outweighs the value of additional context."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Priority order: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "procedural (always included) \u2192 semantic facts (high-value, compact) \u2192 episodic lessons (top 5 by relevance) \u2192 truncate if over budget."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Avoid over-writing: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "let the model "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "propose"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " new facts via "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "extract_and_store_facts"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "; a human or a validation step should confirm before permanent storage."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Separate stores: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "keep episodic and semantic memory in separate files or database tables. Mixing them makes both harder to inspect, debug, and prune."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Goal-Relevant Fact Retrieval"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Passing all semantic facts to every run is wasteful and noisy. A retrieval step filters to only the facts that overlap with the current goal, keeping the context block short and signal-dense."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Retrieve semantically relevant facts using keyword overlap.\n# For production use, replace with embedding-based cosine search.\n\ndef retrieve_relevant_facts(\n    sem: SemanticMemory,\n    query: str,\n    max_facts: int = 5,\n) -> list[Fact]:\n    \"\"\"Return facts whose keys or values overlap with the query.\"\"\"\n    query_words = set(query.lower().split())\n    scored: list[tuple[float, Fact]] = []\n    for fact in sem._facts.values():\n        if isinstance(fact, 'TimestampedFact') and fact.expired:\n            continue\n        fact_words = set(f'{fact.key} {fact.value}'.lower().split())\n        overlap = len(query_words & fact_words)\n        if overlap > 0:\n            scored.append((overlap, fact))\n    scored.sort(key=lambda x: -x[0])\n    return [f for _, f in scored[:max_facts]]\n\ndef focused_context(\n    sem: SemanticMemory,\n    current_goal: str,\n) -> str:\n    facts = retrieve_relevant_facts(sem, current_goal)\n    if not facts:\n        return ''\n    lines = ['Relevant facts for this goal:']\n    lines.extend(f'  {f.key}: {f.value}' for f in facts)\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For agents with large semantic stores (hundreds of facts), replace keyword overlap with embedding similarity: embed the query and each fact's "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "key + value"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " string, then retrieve the top-K by cosine score."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Serialising Semantic Memory"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Save the full semantic store to JSON after each run. On reload, reconstruct "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "TimestampedFact"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " vs plain "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Fact"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " by the presence of the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ttl_seconds"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " key. Expired facts are silently excluded at read time by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "as_context()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json as _json\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSEMANTIC_FILE = Path('semantic_memory.json')\n\ndef save_semantic(sem: SemanticMemory) -> None:\n    data = []\n    for f in sem._facts.values():\n        entry = {\n            'key': f.key,\n            'value': f.value,\n            'source': f.source,\n            'confidence': f.confidence,\n        }\n        if isinstance(f, TimestampedFact):\n            entry['created_at'] = f.created_at\n            entry['ttl_seconds'] = f.ttl_seconds\n        data.append(entry)\n    SEMANTIC_FILE.write_text(_json.dumps(data, indent=2))\n\ndef load_semantic() -> SemanticMemory:\n    sem = SemanticMemory()\n    if not SEMANTIC_FILE.exists():\n        return sem\n    for entry in _json.loads(SEMANTIC_FILE.read_text()):\n        if 'ttl_seconds' in entry:\n            f = TimestampedFact(\n                key=entry['key'], value=entry['value'],\n                source=entry.get('source', ''),\n                confidence=entry.get('confidence', 1.0),\n                created_at=entry.get('created_at', time.time()),\n                ttl_seconds=entry['ttl_seconds'],\n            )\n        else:\n            f = Fact(\n                key=entry['key'], value=entry['value'],\n                source=entry.get('source', ''),\n                confidence=entry.get('confidence', 1.0),\n            )\n        sem._facts[f.key] = f\n    return sem\n"
          }
        ]
